    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Fiber spun from the longest, degummable fibers of the waste of the silk cocoon. It is not as lustrous as reeled silk, which is a continuous fiber.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
